init_text:
How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think it has made it easier to meet people, especially if you are shy or introverted.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It has also made it easier to communicate with people you have met, and to get to know them better.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It has also made it easier to communicate with people, and to get to know them before you meet them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This can be a good thing, but it can also be a bad thing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There are also those that use the apps to find a partner for a one night stand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think that the apps have also made it easier for people to be dishonest, and to lie about their age, or their appearance.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think that dating apps are a good thing, and I would recommend them to anyone.
